item.title: Локомотив — Зенит 4-2 Обзор матча
item.description:
Локомотив — Зенит 4-2 Обзор матча
Lokomotiv stage a remarkable comeback against Zenit Saturday, September 10th, 2011 Lokomotiv Moscow 4 -- Zenit St. Petersburg 2 (Russian Premier League, September 10, 2011) Danko Lazovic curled in a right footed beauty to fire Zenit ahead early doors, and Aleksandr Bukharov curled in a left footed shot in the 31st to leave Lokomotiv in big trouble. Immediately after the restart the hosts netted a lifeline as Victor Obinna scored into an open net from 20-yards out, and Lokomotiv completed their comeback when Felipe Caicedo equalised on the hour. A second former West Ham man, Manuel da Costa, headed Lokomotiv into 3-2 lead as Zenit collapsed. Three minutes from time Manuel da Costa sealed Lokomotiv's amazing turnaround. 10 сентября 2011 года, суббота. 16:30 мск 23-й тур Москва (Россия). Стадион Локомотив. Главный судья: Алексей Николаев (Москва, Россия) Идет 2-й тайм Матч 1 (08.05.2011) - 1:1.
